texts.text: Right, got it. Thanks.
Guys, the other branches are sendin' Dx2 backup.
We can take a breather for now. Let's return to the Hideout.
Finally. I'm wiped.
Stay vigilant. The operation isn't over until we're back safely.
Like this ain't a field trip.
Gotcha. Glad ya got energy for jokes.
C'mon, let's get a move on'.
Phew, I'm deaaaaad.
Shiang Sun, bring my pudding from the fridge—
Please get it yourself. I'm tired too.
Don't be like that. You're closer.
Let's all pipe down. We'll be back to slaying demons soon.
Maybe tell HIM that.
Hah! Hoh! Yah!
...Hey, Jeng Yun. Can I ask what you're doing?
Squats, as you can see.
I wish to be ready at a moment's notice. Care to join me, Gakuto?
Um, I'm good.
Well, everyone's got a routine.
No one get too comfortable.
Indeed. The next battle awaits...
Liberators, your fight with that last demon was superb.
I have high expectations for the next fierce encounter.
Damn it, another angel...
Aww, not this again.
How do they even get in? There's a barrier over the Hideout.
It is nothing against our power.
That's a pretty neat trick.
So, what are the great Divine up to while we're out fightin'?
Watching over you, of course.
You are all quite skilled. Our intervention is unnecessary.
That's a nice way to spin it. You're just slackin' on the job.
If you saw, then you'd know that last demon was formidable.
Couldn't you have at least aided us?
What are you talking about? The others must have told you.
You are soldiers in God's Army. Our weapons.
As your wielders, we've determined there is no need for us to fight.
So, it is only natural for our weapons to fight in our stead.
...Y'all are a hive mind. This argument is goin' nowhere.
Thanks for comin' all this way, but you should just go.
Talkin' to you is a waste of time.
Agreed. Well then, do rest up.
And fight passionately as members of the Lord's Army...
Man. Communication really ain't their forte.
No kidding. Now we're more stressed than ever.
Well, let's deal with it later. Right now...
We must first think of a way to defeat Rahab.
Yes, thank you. Back to business.
Keep chillin' out, folks. I only need those brains movin'.
Like I said, a drawn-out fight will only work against us.
So, let's think of a way to take down their boss.
Even part of an idea is fine. If you've got one, speak up.
How about you, Shiori?
Nope. Pass.
You didn't even try...
Listen, I said so before.
Our main problem is that only two can travel at once.
If we could send a few more, we'd be in business.
But as it stands our options are few and this guy is a powerhouse.
So really, we need to figure out how to send more people.
Unluckily for us, Kokoro said that's impossible.
Basically, we're stuck.
So, did I spell it out enough for you blockheads?
Yes, I think we get the picture.
Um, hey. I didn't mention this before, but...
Huh? Oh, right.
You got some kinda plan, Ririn?
Well, I wouldn't call it a "plan" exactly.
So far, we've assumed we need to fight in the other world.
But if that won't work...
Why not call Rahab here instead?
To this world...?
That's not a bad idea.
Like Takadono said, we'll be at a disadvantage over there.
But if he comes to us, we'll have more leeway.
Reverse thinkin', huh?
Nice one, Ririn!
Hehe. The rest of you just don't think outside the box!
Right, Shionyan?
...I'll admit it's a pretty good idea. For you, anyway.
So, how exactly do we get Rahab over here?
Well, uh...
Let's all put our heads together!
*Sigh*
I'm sorry, everyone.
If only I had more information, we wouldn't be so stuck...
Hey now, don't blame yourself.
But...
Everyone, there's been an emergency!
What's wrong, Himika?
Please go outside!
A powerful magic is fast approaching!
A powerful magic... It can't be!
Let's go!
Whoa, what the hell is that?!
The sky is distorted?
This aura...!
>A sensation strikes Rika, and a moment later—
>An enormous head emerges from the warped sky.
Where is she? The human woman who maimed me.
I've come to devour your head.
Now, show yourself.
He's bigger than I thought. So that must be...
Yes, Rahab. I can't believe he came all this way.
He seems weirdly focused on Rika...
Did you do something to him?
Who knows? We did fight, though.
If anything, maybe it's because I hit the scale under his chin.
The scale under his chin, huh?
That was probably his inverted scale.
"Inverted scale"?
The scale beneath a dragon's chin is said to be inverted.
A dragon's wrath will burn until they kill whoever struck it.
So, he's after me...
Rika and Newbie, you're the real MVPs!
Thanks to you, he did all the legwork for us!
Awesome!
Is this really a good thing?
...Yes. It's truly a blessing in disguise.
I believe so. This is our chance, Newbie.
The time has come to defeat Rahab.
That solves our main problem. Now on to...
The fight! Let's do it, y'all!
You're goin' down, Rahab!
